Class FishEye

java.lang.Object
  com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.UIObject
      com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.Widget
          com.objetdirect.tatami.client.AbstractDojo
              com.objetdirect.tatami.client.FishEye
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.google.gwt.user.client.EventListener, com.google.gwt.user.client.WindowResizeListener, HasDojo
public class FishEye
extends AbstractDojo
implements com.google.gwt.user.client.WindowResizeListener

Menu similar to the fish eye menu on the Mac OS. Each item of the fish eye menu is clickable. A command (GWT) can be associated to each icons and will be invoked each times that an item will be selected

This component is an encapsulation GWT of Dojo components. Warning the widget exist under 3 faces :

  • a GWT widget (this!)
  • a Dojo widget (which play the role of 'this' for GWT)
  • a structur of DOM elements, the only exploitable presentation by the navigator.

Author:
Henry

FishEye

public FishEye(int itemWidth,
               int itemHeight,
               int itemMaxWidth,
               int itemMaxHeight,
               java.lang.String orientation,
               int effectUnits,
               int itemPadding,
               java.lang.String attachEdge,
               java.lang.String labelEdge,
               boolean conservativeTrigger)
Creates a FishEye menu with no icons

Parameters:
itemWidth - width of menu item (in pixels) in it's dormant state (when the mouse is far away)
itemHeight - height of menu item (in pixels) in it's dormant state (when the mouse is far away)
itemMaxWidth - width of menu item (in pixels) in it's fully enlarged state (when the mouse is directly over it)
itemMaxHeight - height of menu item (in pixels) in it's fully enlarged state (when the mouse is directly over it)
orientation - orientation of the menu, either HORIZONTAL or VERTICAL
effectUnits - controls how much reaction the menu makes, relative to the distance of the mouse from the menu
itemPadding - padding (in pixels) betweeen each menu item
attachEdge - controls the border that the menu items don't expand past; for example, if set to "top", then the menu items will drop downwards as they expand. Possible values are : CENTER, TOP, BOTTOM, LEFT, RIGHT
labelEdge - controls were the labels show up in relation to the menu item icons. Possible values are : CENTER, TOP, BOTTOM, LEFT, RIGHT
conservativeTrigger - if true, don't start enlarging menu items until mouse is over an image; if false, start enlarging menu items as the mouse moves near them.
